<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
    xml:id="entry_æzmīlyn" xml:lang="os">
    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>æzmīlyn</orth><form type="inflected"
            subtype="ptcp"><orth>æzmīld</orth></form></form>
    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>æzmelun</orth><form type="inflected"
            subtype="ptcp"><orth>æzmilt</orth></form></form>
    <sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>прясть особым образом</q>
            </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>spin in a particular way</q>
            </cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>прясть мягко, не круто</q>
            </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>spin tenderly, not severely</q>
            </cit></sense></sense>
    <sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>сдваивать нити пряжи</q>
        </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>double yarn threads</q>
        </cit></sense>
    <sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>подготовлять шерсть для пряжи в виде колец, наматываемых на руку</q>
        </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>prepare wool for yarn in the form of rings wound on the hand</q>
        </cit><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/></sense>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Возможно, метатеза из %iæm%i-%izīlyn%i (см. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_zīlyn"/> ‘крутить’ и префикс <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æm-"/>-). Если
        же предполагать в начале преверб %iyz%i- (<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
            ><lang/><w>uz-</w></mentioned>), то основу %imīl%i- | %imel%i- можно связать с
        индоевропейским <mentioned xml:lang="ga"><lang/><w>*mer</w></mentioned>, которое находим в
            <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
            ><lang/><w>μέρμīς</w><gloss><q>нить</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                ><w>μηρύω</w><gloss><q>наматываю</q></gloss></mentioned>, и пр. Из осетинского
        усвоено <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/><w>zmelt</w></mentioned> (= <mentioned
            xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/><w>æzmilt</w><gloss><q>вид
        пряжи</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It is probably a metathesis from %iæm%i-%izīlyn%i (see <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_zīlyn"/> ‘spin’ and the prefix <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æm-"/>-). If
        we suppose that in the begining there is the preverb %iyz%i- (<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
                ><lang/><w>uz-</w></mentioned>), the stem %imīl%i- | %imel%i- may be connected with
        the Indo-European <mentioned xml:lang="ga"><lang/><w>*mer</w></mentioned>, which is found in
            <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
            ><lang/><w>μέρμīς</w><gloss><q>thread</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                ><w>μηρύω</w><gloss><q>I wind (round)</q></gloss></mentioned>, etc. <mentioned
            xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/><w>zmelt</w></mentioned> (= <mentioned
            xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/><w>æzmilt</w><gloss><q>a type of
            yarn</q></gloss></mentioned>) was borrowed from Ossetic.</etym>
</entry>
